description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you an experienced communications professional who wants to be part of a high performing and dynamic team supporting the NHS in our capital city?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a shared ambition for London to be the world’s healthiest global city, and the best global city in which to receive health and care services for 9.2 million Londoners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Deputy Head of Strategic Communications, you will be the lead for our communications team who are responsible for managing, protecting and enhancing the reputation of NHS in London through clear and coherent messaging via the media, Parliamentary briefings and campaigns. You will also lead the provision of an efficient, effective and professionally co-ordinated strategic communications function capable of meeting all statutory, regulatory and NHS requirements ensuring alignment with the values and aims of the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also join a team of committed, passionate and hard-working individuals who want to make a difference for our NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will be enthusiastic, creative, customer-focused, energetic, flexible and unflappable. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a short term secondment / fixed term opportunity to start immediately, finishing on 31st December 2020. This is to cover a short term vacancy due to temporary vacancies within the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Emer Delaney&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Head of Strategic Communications - London Region&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: emer.delaney1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 07860180486&lt;/p&gt;
